pr_title: Hello World from GCP Scanner Visualizer
pr_body:
## Description

This is the first PR for creating the visualization tool for the GCP scanner output

## Changes Made

- Create the React project in the `visualization_tool` folder
- Setup linting and formatting
- Add the `gui` folder in the GCP scanner to include static files and Python script to launch a flask server to host the tool
- Add new command `gcp-scanner-visualizer` to launch vis tool
- Add `Flask` to Python requirements

## Additional Notes

Currently the build script for the react project outputs static files in `src/gcp_scnneer/gui/static` but this folder is not getting added to the final gcp scanner package after the build because of this issue #186

pr_title: fix: use MANIFEST.in for controlling files in the distribution
pr_body:
## Description

Get rid of using the hatch system and instead use MANIFEST.in file which is compatible with setuptools system

## Changes Made
- remove `hatch.build` section from `pyproject.toml` file
- add `MANIFEST.in` file to exclude test files


## Related Issues
#186

pr_title: feat: Extend parser to parse most of resources
pr_body:
## Description

Change parser implementation to a more generic one that can parse most resources types

![image](https://github.com/google/gcp_scanner/assets/30212455/7b53851f-a208-4781-b062-5bb14ce36485)


## Additional Notes

The types supported by the tool are:
- `Compute Instance`
- `Compute Disk`
- `Compute Image`
- `Machine Image`
- `Compute Snapshot`
- `Managed Zone`
- `SQL Instance`
- `Cloud Function`
- `Dns Policies`
- `Pubsub Sub`

These types are defined in  `availableResourceTypes` in `src/types/resources.ts` 
Other types have special structures in the output file which we can handle later

pr_title: chore: Replace flask with http.server python module  for serving visualization tool
pr_body:
## Description

Instead of adding `flask` to the project dependencies to create the server that hosts the tool, use the already existing Python `http.server` module for creating the server

## Changes Made
- Change implementationon of `gui/app.py`
- Fix some errors related to building the visualization tool
- Remove `static` word from tool URLs

## Additional Notes
The following steps to build the tool and test it after the build
1. `cd visualization_tool/`
2. `npm run build`
3. `cd  cd ../src/gcp_scanner/gui/`
4. `python app.py`

pr_title: feat: Easier flow for uploading files to the visualizer
pr_body:
## Description

Provide a more easier flow for adding multiple files to the visualizer 

![Peek 2023-09-19 14-31](https://github.com/google/gcp_scanner/assets/30212455/c03bc9fe-151b-454b-b011-5cfffe41abef)


## Changes Made
- Separate parsing logic from `Controller.ts` to `parser/parser.ts`
- Refactor `UploadMenu` component

## Related Issues
#277 #279

## Additional Notes
The Usage guide needs to be updated but I will delay it as the next PR will add changes to the UI

- Group roles by project and remove project name from role name
- Update usage document
